    <briefdescription>
<para>Pure 32-bit phase-accumulator NCO. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Phase increments by phase_inc each sample and wraps naturally at 2^32. Three output mappings:</para>
<para>nco_steps_u32 raw accumulator value [0, 2^32) nco_steps_u32_scaled (uint64)phase * nmax &gt;&gt; 32 → [0, nmax) nco_steps_u32_ovf raw phase + per-sample carry flag</para>
<para>nmax=0 in nco_steps_u32_scaled is treated identically to nco_steps_u32 (returns raw accumulator unchanged).</para>
<para>Normalised-frequency → phase_inc conversion: phase_inc = floor((norm_freq mod 1.0) × 2^32)</para>
<para>Negative frequencies fold correctly: −0.25 → phase_inc = 3×2^30.</para>
<para>reset() zeroes phase only; norm_freq and nmax are unchanged.</para>
<para>Lifecycle: nco_create → (steps / reset)* → nco_destroy</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structnco__state__t" kindref="compound">nco_state_t</ref><sp/>*nco<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="nco__core_8h_1ab5b4f944d9172b609a9a760bf3e2b3ff" kindref="member">nco_create</ref>(0.25,<sp/>0);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint32_t<sp/>out[4];</highlight></codeline>
